# Cursor AI Rules — Coding Guidelines Integration
# This file instructs Cursor AI to follow the project's coding standards.

## Primary Reference

Read `llm.md` in the project root FIRST. It is the single entry point for understanding and enforcing all coding guidelines in this repository.

## Quick Rules (CODE RED — Zero Tolerance)

1. Zero nested `if` — flatten with early returns
2. All booleans start with `is`, `has`, `can`, `should`, `was`, `will`
3. No magic strings — use enum/typed constants
4. Max 15 lines per function
5. No boolean flag parameters — split into named methods
6. Blank line before `return`/`throw`
7. No `else` after `return`/`throw`/`continue`/`break`

### Go-Specific
- Use `apperror.Result[T]`, never `(T, error)`
- Use `apperror.New()`/`Wrap()`, never `fmt.Errorf()`
- Use `type Variant byte` + `iota`, never string enums

### TypeScript-Specific
- Use `Promise.all()` for independent async calls

### PHP-Specific
- Use `->isEqual()` for enum comparison, never `===`

## Context Loading

For full details, load files in this order from `spec/02-coding-guidelines/03-coding-guidelines-spec/06-ai-optimization/`:
1. `04-condensed-master-guidelines.md` (start here)
2. `01-anti-hallucination-rules.md`
